{{Quote|Attention Hangar 84G, there is a prison riot in progress. A contingent of the 501st is inbound from an exterior inspection. Join up with the squad mates in the hangar, and quell this riot.|An Imperial officer|<ref name="BFII">''[[Star Wars: Battlefront II]]''</ref>}}
'''Hangar 84G''' was a hangar bay onboard the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|first Death Star]], in operation during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. This hangar was located in proximity to the battle station's [[Superlaser Fire Control]] Room and the detention blocks.<ref name="BFII" />

Hangar 84G became a battleground when a number of [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] prisoners [[Death Star Uprising|escaped]] from their cells on the Death Star and attempted to flee the battle station. A group of would-be escapees attacked Hangar 84G, hoping to steal a transport. However, the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperials]] had deployed the [[501st Legion/Legends|501st Legion]] in response to the prison break, and these elite troopers were able to successfully defend the hangar bay and their [[Sentinel-class landing craft/Legends|''Sentinel''-class landing craft]]. They also managed to secure the [[Detention Block 2180|detention block]] where the riot originated. Finally The 501st moved deeper into the station, killing all the escapees and destroying their transport in [[Hangar 85G]].<ref name="BFII" />

Hangar 84G was destroyed when the Death Star exploded during the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]].<ref name="Episode IV">{{Film|IV}}</ref>

